A strange turn of events leads the Dragon, Tohru, to work as Miss Kobayashi's maid. She occasionally (that's a lie, she often) causes trouble for her beloved Miss Kobayashi while blending into human society and splendidly (that's a lie, only mediocrely) carrying out her maid duties. Her fellow dragons, Kanna, Lucoa, Fafnir, and Elma all find their own places to fit in as well and enjoy interspecies interactions with the humans. Yet while they're all enjoying that laid-back and occasionally turbulent left, the threat of a new Dragon swoops down upon Miss Kobayashi.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Comedy, Ecchi, Romance, Slice of Life

Announced on Yom's Twitter, a web anime adaptation of Ganbare, Douki-chan. The story follows an office lady, Douki-chan, who is working with Douki-kun in an office. Unbeknownst to Douki-kun, Douki-chan secretly has feelings for him. As Douki-chan struggles to confess her feelings, her rivals, both the kohai and senpai, continue to vie for his affection.
Mama Tomo to Sodateru Love Come

Komamoto Kyota is a high school boy who dotes on his 3-year-old sister. His parents both work, so he handles all the housework and childcare at home. Akiyama Sumi is a beautiful, smart, but solitary girl whose intimidating presence keeps everyone at arm's length. When Kyota went to his sister's kindergarten entrance ceremony, he found Sumi there with flushed cheeks, snapping pictures like a pro photographer. "Gosh, how adorable...... she is!" They became friends and gradually grew closer as they learned that they are both taking care of younger siblings. They cook together, help each other pick up the kids from kindergarten, and go on holiday outings. Yes, their relationship is truly that of "mommy's friend." A romantic comedy about child-raising!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
